  "text": "The baseline characteristics of patients enrolled into the study are shown in Table 1 . Body composition, metabolic, inflammatory, and fibrinolytic parameters were similar between the study groups at baseline (all P > 0.05). Mean waist circumference was 104 AE 10 cm, and mean waist-to-hip ratio was 1.05 AE 0.06. Mean CRP was elevated at more than 4 mg/l in both groups. Mean VAT was more than 170 cm 2 in both groups, far exceeding thresholds that have been associated with increased cardiovascular risk [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
